race.description: Brad Widdup Racing Provincial Maiden Plate
race.comment: Open race. EX WIFE (1) returned from 13 months on the sidelines with an encouraging effort over 1000m at Kembla, fighting hard in a busy finish only to go under narrowly. Sure to take a lot from that run and the extra 100m should suit. EMERY (3) returns from a six-month lay-off and is a threat. Placed at both runs last prep including a close second when resuming over this distance at the Kensington track. Trialling well and only needs to reproduce that first-up run from the last campaign to be right in the finish. BUBBLES PLEASE (6) is a half-sister to the promising Idle Flyer on debut for Kris Lees. Trials have been okay - suspect she will have more to offer come race day. CRATHIE KIRK (7) is another debutante from the Lees stable whose trial form has been reasonable. Betting holds the key. GRAND CAROUSEL (13) has not raced since an eye-catching fourth on debut over 1000m at Kembla in May. Trialling well and looks set for a bright return.
